headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points and hit five 3-pointers to help the Boston Celtics run past the Utah Jazz 126-97 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 30 as Celtics use 3s, defense to smother Jazz 126-97

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 18 of Indiana’s franchise-record 50 assists and the Pacers routed the Atlanta Hawks 150-116 on Friday night for their sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton has 18 of Indiana's team-record 50 assists, Pacers rout Hawks 150-116 for 6th win a row

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — The Nets hadn't won in the new year and their leading scorer hadn't even made a shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets open 32-point lead, beat Thunder 124-115 to end 5-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points, Jarrett Allen had his sixth straight double-double and the Cleveland Cavaliers rolled to their second easy win in three nights over Washington, beating the Wizards 114-90 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell's 26 points, another double-double by Jarrett Allen send Cavs past Wizards 114-90

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson playfully tried to escape a media scrum in front of his locker by announcing that Josh Hart was ready to talk to reporters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 29 points to lead Knicks past 76ers 128-92 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Coby White had 22 points, 10 rebounds and six assists, and the Chicago Bulls welcomed back Zach LaVine and Nikola Vucevic with a 104-91 victory over Miles Bridges and the Charlotte Hornets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 22 points as the Chicago Bulls beat the Charlotte Hornets 104-91

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 24 points, Karl-Anthony Towns had 22 and the Western Conference-leading Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Houston Rockets 122-95 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 24 points, West-leading Timberwolves beat Rockets 122-95

events.name: LA Clippers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Paul George made six 3-pointers and scored 24 points, Kawhi Leonard added 19 points and nine rebounds, and the surging Los Angeles Clippers beat the New Orleans Pelicans 111-95 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul George, Kawhi Leonard lead surging Clippers past Pelicans, 111-95

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 24 points with fellow All-Star Luka Doncic sidelined by a sore ankle, and the Dallas Mavericks swept a two-game home set against Portland by beating the Trail Blazers 139-103 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 24 with Luka Doncic out, Mavs finish sweep of Blazers with 139-103 win

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero was pleased with his first career triple-double. What made it even better was its central role in a stirring comeback.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero records 1st triple-double, hits go-ahead free throws as Magic hold off Nuggets 122-120

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen is usually an afterthought for the opposing team, which makes some sense considering there are other Phoenix Suns to worry about like All-Star shooters Devin Booker and Bradley Beal.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grayson Allen ties Phoenix record with career-high 9 3-pointers, Suns beat Heat 113-97

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Moments after a hard-fought victory to finish back-to-back games at home, the Golden State Warriors found out they will be without veteran leader Chris Paul for the unforeseeable future.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 26 points to help Warriors hold off Pistons, 113-109

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James didn't sugarcoat his increasingly sour feelings after the Los Angeles Lakers spiraled to their 10th loss in 13 games Friday night, falling 127-113 to the Memphis Grizzlies.
headlines.shortLinkText: Frustrated LeBron sounds off on Lakers' struggles after 10th loss in 13 games, 127-113 to Memphis

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 24 points, 15 rebounds and 11 assists for his second consecutive triple-double, and the Sacramento Kings held off the Toronto Raptors 135-130 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis records another triple-double as Kings hold off Raptors 135-130
